column14:
The Natural Wine Shoppe Delivery Instructions:
If the garage door is down, there is a keypad on the right side of the outside entrance where you can put in a code to open the garage door. The code is:
*8637430#
This code is the same to gain access to the storage facility and access to the elevator as well.
Type the code in the box to the right of glass sliding and then again in the elevator to go to the 3rd floor.
Once you are on the third floor there are 2 units that you can place the deliveries in (3151/3160). 
To get to the units you will exit the elevator to the right and go down the second aisle to on your left. 
Lock Combination Instructions:
Squeeze together lock arm 3x (should hear clicking sound when you squeeze lock arm and lock together).
Input arrow code: Left, Left, Down, Right (  )
Should be able to pull lock open after inputting this code
If you have any issues at all please call 703-863-7430 and ask for Greg. Thank you!
column21: 2800 8th Street Northeast  District of Columbia DC United States 20017

column14:
Delivery Instructions, ie. Front or Rear etc. - 

Please note that all deliveries arriving at 1401 MUST arrive through the loading dock alley (off of 14th st) or on Pennsylvania Ave.  Delivery trucks can NEVER be parked and unloaded on 14th street due to an agreement with the neighbors. 

Also, the loading dock alley is narrow and trucks cannot make the turn around onto Ives street at the end so all trucks must either turn around in the loading dock or back into the alley from 14th street.  All trucks should enter and exit on 14th street only.  

If unloading on Pennsylvania Ave., please do not load into the residential door.  You may wheel pallets around the 14th St. side doors or into the corner doors and down the stairs.

column14:
Inside the mall, we are located on level M2. Vendors typically park in one of two places:
1) Park in the loading dock of the mall. Wine will then need to be wheeled up to our space (level M2, on the opposite end of the mall from the loading dock).
2) If there is space along the curb on Wilson Blvd, in front of True Foods/Ted's Bulletin, some drivers pull up/park along the curb, and then just wheel the wine in through the mall's main entrance, and up one level to our space.

The drivers will go past our main entrance/gate, and right before the entrance to Macy's there is a door on the right, which leads into our back hallway. There are two gray/silver doors in that hallway, both of which are for our space. The drivers can use either door to get in.
